      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i'm not talking about some massive tech experiment, i'm talking about the actual physics of it. like, if every system has a resonant frequency, why wouldn't a storm cell have one too? it's just math. if i'm hitting a frequency that matches the pressure oscillation, it has to do something. \n\ncan you just look at the physics for me? if a storm cell has a certain cycle or vibration, what would the math look like to find the counter-frequency? just give me the theoretical calculation, i just want to see if the numbers even make sense.",
